modName: Cara Delevingne inspired Racemenu preset (Real Women of Skyrim skin)
summary: "2nd" Cara Delevingne Racemenu preset for Skyrim
descriptionHtml:
[center][size=2]|
[/size]|
|
[size=4][b][u]DESCRIPTION:[/u][/b][/size]
This is Cara Delevingne inspired Racemenu preset using Real Women of Skyrim skin as the base of the skin,
[u]without it, the preset will never be look the same as i intended to be.[/u]

I started at choosing the "right" base preset by checking out each default Skyrim presets provided for human race,
and i ended up with Imperia[u]l[/u]'s preset #6.
There, i started moving the variables.
I never utilized the sculpting feature of the Racemenu for i'm not capable of doing so.
|
|
|
|
|
[u][color=#ffff00][b][size=4]DISCLAIMER:[/size][/b][/color]
[/u][color=#ffff00]If you think the preset doesn't meets your criteria and my depictions for the preset's supposed to looked like is way off,
I'm glad for you at stopping by, feel free to pass and pretend like this post never existed.[/color]
|
|
|
|
|[/center][center][color=#ff0000][size=4][b][u]REQUIREMENTS:[/u][/b][/size][/color]
[url=https://rd.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/29624]Racemenu[/url] (along side of it's prerequisites ofcourse)
[url=https://rd.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/85649?]Real Women of Skyrim - Texture Overhaul CBBE UNP - Male and Child WIP - fomod[/url] (i'm using the Makeup provided by this mod)
[url=https://rd.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/72825/?]Maevan's eye brows[/url] (Pick the Standalone, High resolution, Black ([u]not the Dynamic[/u]))
[url=https://rd.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/13722/?]The Eyes Of Beauty[/url] (PLAYER)[/center][center]You will need the Brows & Eyes MODS as mentioned above, for the "custom" Brows and Eyes that i provided as OPTIONAL,
with intention to match up the look i tailored for the preset.
|
|
|
|
|
[color=#00ffff][size=4][b][u]POSSIBLY Q & A:
[/u][/b][/size]
[/color][i][b][color=#00ffff]SSE?[/color][/b][/i][color=#00ffff]
[/color]I only have the so called "old rim", so it's impossible to begin with.

[color=#00ffff][i][b]Was the preset intended for...[/b][/i][/color]
Yes, this preset only viable for Human races [u]but not for[/u] Elven, Beast & Orcs.
I do include a folder on Misc files, showing the preset on each race.

[i][b][color=#00ffff]I do not use the skin you required for this preset!
[/color][/b][/i]There's a reason why i required it.

[color=#00ffff][i][b]Why Cara???[/b][/i][/color]
Why ask?

[color=#00ffff][i][b]I can do better with ECE, with my eyes closed, 1 arm tied behind my back while holding a coffee mug with my toes!!![/b][/i][/color]
Good to hear. :)

[color=#00ffff][i][b]You seem like a toxic person![/b][/i]
[/color]I'm good at containing the very least. :)
